h3cVrrpExt.name: h3cVrrpExt
h3cVrrpExt.contactinfo: Huawei-3Com Technologies Co.,Ltd. Shang-Di Information Industry Base, Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Zip:100085 Http://www.huawei-3com.com
h3cVrrpExt.description: This MIB describes objects used for managing Virtual Router Redundancy Protocol (VRRP) routers.

h3cVrrpExtTable.name: h3cVrrpExtTable
h3cVrrpExtTable.description: Table extends for a VRRP router which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of h3cVrrpExtEntry items.

h3cVrrpExtEntry.name: h3cVrrpExtEntry
h3cVrrpExtEntry.description: An entry in the h3cVrrpExtTable containing the status values of a virtual router.

h3cVrrpExtTrackInterface.name: h3cVrrpExtTrackInterface
h3cVrrpExtTrackInterface.description: This value is the ifIndex that identifies which interface the virtual router tracked.

h3cVrrpExtPriorityReduce.name: h3cVrrpExtPriorityReduce
h3cVrrpExtPriorityReduce.description: This value identifies how much priority of a virtual router will be reduced/increased when the interface tracked is down/up.

h3cVrrpExtRowStatus.name: h3cVrrpExtRowStatus
h3cVrrpExtRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. Setting this object to active(1) or createAndGo(4) results in the addition of the ifIndex tracked by a virtual router. Destroying the entry removes the tracked ifIndex from the virtual router. Other values is not supported now.
